Spatial cell clustering of MERFISH data by MEcell

Qi Liu

19 June, 2025

  • Load the library and the seurat object
  • Build the microenvironment-aware SNN graph (named MEcell), followed by clustering
  • subclustering on the microenvironment-aware SNN to find region-specific cell subtypes

Load the library and the seurat object

library(MEcell)
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)


# The data have been log-normalized, scaled and RunPCA using Seurat
#The Seurat object contains raw counts,normalized data, and PCA embeddings

obj<-readRDS(url("https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/84qkslotuyfa3yby76rke/merfish.rds?rlkey=3lovwnc75kn2qjka4ivw8gv05&dl=1"))

#if data have not been pre-processed, please normalize and scale the data and RunPCA
#obj<-NormalizeData(obj) %>% ScaleData(features=rownames(obj)) %>% RunPCA(features=rownames(obj))

Build the microenvironment-aware SNN graph (named MEcell), followed by clustering

# build the microenvironment-aware SNN graph (named MEcell)
obj<-MEcell(obj)

#clustering on the MEcell SNN graph
obj<-FindClusters(obj,graph.name = "MEcell",verbose = F)

#visualizing cell clustering 
SpatialDimPlot(obj,group.by="MEcell_res.0.8")+ ggtitle("MEcell clustering")+theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

subclustering on the microenvironment-aware SNN to find region-specific cell subtypes

#two OD subtypes: one densely localized within white matter and another sparsely distributed outside white matter 
# subclustering on the MEcell SNN graph
obj<-FindSubCluster(obj,cluster=2,graph.name = "MEcell")

SpatialDimPlot(obj[,obj$MEcell_res.0.8==2],group.by="sub.cluster",pt.size.factor = 3)+ ggtitle("Two OD subtypes")+theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

##three region-specific ependymal subtypes 
obj<-FindSubCluster(obj,cluster=5,graph.name = "MEcell")
SpatialDimPlot(obj[,obj$MEcell_res.0.8==5],group.by="sub.cluster",pt.size.factor = 3)+ ggtitle("Three ependymal subtypes")+theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))
